    "description": "<p><p>2023.10.3. 1 black and white photograph, 4 x 5 1/2 in., on brown cardboard. Studio photograph of man seated, wearing WWI Red Cross arm band on left arm. Front of card is labeled \"Schriver and Kibler,\" \"1213 N. 3rd Street, Harrisburg, PA.\" Back of photograph is handwritten: \"Cory W. Brady of Pataskala, Licking County, Ohio. Corps reserve ambulance company.\" Another hand in blue ink pen has written: \"Auntie nursed this boy.\" This item is owned by the Museum of Nursing History,&nbsp; <a href=\"https://nursinghistory.org/\" shape=\"rect\">https://nursinghistory.org/</a>.</p></p>",
